dct_title_s: Map of part of the Argentine Republic to illustrate the paper by Mr. Consul Hutchinson
dct_description_sm: Mr. Hutchinson's routes shown in red. Relief shown by hachures. Forest, marsh, and salt steppe areas shown graphically. Deserted settlements of Pozo de Quinti, Pozo de Sixto, Pozo de Campi, la Cañada, Pozo Antonio, and Pozo Olumpa are shown. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 34 (1864), pp. 226-45; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.34 1864.
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1864.
